Class SingleElementMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.beaftech.collique.SingleElementMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type
    V - the value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>

    public class SingleElementMap<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<K,V>
    Single key/value pair implementation of Map. This implementation permits null values and the null key, and provides all optional map operations with some restrictions on element addition as this map can only contains one key/value pair. More precisely, put(Object, Object) and putAll(Map) operations will throw UnsupportedOperationException when trying to add another key/value pair to this map.
    Author:
    Arnould Guidat
